{
  "esm": "0.4.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "calc_direct_fluxes",
    "description": "Direct solar beam actinic fluxes for all 18 Fast-JX wavelength bands as a function of cosine solar zenith angle (CSZA) and pressure (P). Migrated from GasChem.jl src/Fast-JX.jl:1082 (calc_direct_fluxes, @register_symbolic). Implements Beer-Lambert direct-beam attenuation through the GEOS-Chem 73-level hybrid vertical grid with Rayleigh + O\u2082 + O\u2083 optical depths and spherical geometry air mass factors. The gt-p3ep gap is resolved by precomputing over a 61-CSZA \u00d7 73-P grid and expressing each of the 18 output fluxes as an interp.bilinear lookup.",
    "tags": [
      "gaschem",
      "fast-jx",
      "photolysis",
      "registered_function",
      "actinic_flux",
      "direct_beam",
      "beer_lambert",
      "interp-bilinear"
    ],
    "created": "2026-05-22T00:00:00Z",
    "authors": [
      "GasChem.jl contributors",
      "EarthSciModels migration (esm-2u1x)"
    ],
    "references": [
      {
        "citation": "Neu, J.L., Prather, M.J., and Penner, J.E. (2007), Global atmospheric chemistry: Integrating over fractional cloud cover, J. Geophys. Res., 112, D11306, doi:10.1029/2006JD008007. \u2014 Source for the Fast-JX scheme."
      },
      {
        "citation": "Source: GasChem.jl/src/Fast-JX.jl (commit 8c12c048482b515fb8eb2110bf8ab4b4f4e71309). calc_direct_fluxes(CSZA, P) returns a vector of 18 direct-beam actinic fluxes. Depends on direct_solar_beam_box, OD_total (74\u00d718 optical depth matrix), z_profile (74-element height vector), top_flux (18-element TOA flux vector)."
      }
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "calc_direct_fluxes": {
      "reference": {
        "notes": "source_ref: GasChem.jl@8c12c048482b515fb8eb2110bf8ab4b4f4e71309:src/Fast-JX.jl:1082\n\nUpstream definition:\n  function calc_direct_fluxes(CSZA, P)\n      direct_flux_factor = direct_solar_beam_box(OD_total, CSZA, z_profile, P)\n      fluxes = top_flux .* direct_flux_factor\n      return fluxes\n  end\n  @register_symbolic calc_direct_fluxes(CSZA, P)\n\ndirect_solar_beam_box uses:\n  - find_closest_pressure_index: snaps P to nearest of 73 P_levels (piecewise-constant in P)\n  - sphere2J: spherical-geometry air mass factors for the slanted solar beam path\n  - Beer-Lambert: exp(-\u03c4) attenuation with Rayleigh + O\u2082 + O\u2083 optical depths (OD_total)\n  - top_flux: 18-band TOA solar flux vector\n\nGrid axes:\n  CSZA axis (61 pts): cosSZA_vals = [-0.2, -0.18, ..., 1.0] (step 0.02)\n  P axis (73 pts): P_levels reversed to ascending order, from ~1 Pa (TOA) to 101325 Pa (surface)\n  P_levels = Ap + Bp \u00d7 101325 Pa (GEOS-Chem 72-layer hybrid sigma-pressure coordinate)\n\nOutput variables F_{wl} correspond to GasChem WL array wavelengths [nm]:\n  187, 191, 193, 196, 202, 208, 211, 214, 261, 267, 277, 295, 303, 310, 316, 333, 380, 574\n\nAccuracy note: the bilinear lookup is exact at grid intersections. Off-grid CSZA queries\nmay incur larger errors for bands 10-12 (261-277 nm) near the surface, where the Beer-Lambert\nattenuation has a steep transition in CSZA (transition from full absorption to partial transmission).\nCSZA step 0.02 is sufficient for bands 1-9 (always 0 at surface) and 13-18 (slowly varying).\n\nFlat extrapolation at all edges:\n  CSZA < -0.2 \u2192 CSZA = -0.2 (deep night, all fluxes = 0)\n  CSZA > 1.0 \u2192 CSZA = 1.0 (overhead sun)\n  P < ~1 Pa \u2192 top-of-atmosphere (\u2248 top_flux \u00d7 1)\n  P > 101325 Pa \u2192 surface values (highest attenuation)"
      },
      "tolerance": {
        "rel": 1e-09,
        "abs": 1e-30
      },
      "variables": {
        "CSZA": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "1",
          "default": 0.5,
          "description": "Cosine of the solar zenith angle (dimensionless, clipped to [-0.2, 1.0] with flat extrapolation)."
        },
        "P": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "Pa",
          "default": 101325.0,
          "description": "Air pressure (Pa). Mapped to the nearest level in the 73-level GEOS-Chem hybrid vertical grid (P_levels)."
        },
        "F_187": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1/s",
          "description": "Direct solar beam actinic flux at Fast-JX wavelength band 1 (187 nm) (s\u207b\u00b9). = top_flux[1] \u00d7 Beer-Lambert attenuation factor. Bilinearly interpolated from precomputed 61-CSZA \u00d7 73-P table.",
